trans-unit.source: Exposes an enumerator, which supports a simple iteration over a non-generic collection.
trans-unit.target: 公开枚举数，该枚举数支持在非泛型集合上进行简单迭代。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> is the base interface for all non-generic collections that can be enumerated.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> 是可以枚举的所有非泛型集合的基接口。

trans-unit.source: For the generic version of this interface see <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601?displayProperty=nameWithType>.
trans-unit.target: 有关此接口的泛型版本，请参阅<xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601?displayProperty=nameWithType>。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> contains a single method, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable.GetEnumerator%2A>, which returns an <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> 包含单个方法<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable.GetEnumerator%2A>，它将返回<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> provides the ability to iterate through the collection by exposing a <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> property and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> methods.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> 提供了通过公开循环访问集合的能力<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>属性和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>方法。

trans-unit.source: It is a best practice to implement <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> on your collection classes to enable the `foreach` (`For Each` in Visual Basic) syntax, however implementing <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> is not required.
trans-unit.target: 若要实现最佳做法是<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>上您的集合类，以启用`foreach`(`For Each`在 Visual Basic 中) 语法，但是实现<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>不是必需的。

trans-unit.source: If your collection does not implement <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>, you must still follow the iterator pattern to support this syntax by providing a `GetEnumerator` method that returns an interface, class or struct.
trans-unit.target: 如果你的集合不实现<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>，您仍必须按照要通过提供支持此语法的迭代器模式`GetEnumerator`返回接口、 类或结构的方法。

trans-unit.source: When using Visual Basic, you must provide an <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> implementation, which is returned by `GetEnumerator`.
trans-unit.target: 如果使用 Visual Basic，则必须提供<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>实现，它可以返回`GetEnumerator`。

trans-unit.source: When developing with C# you must provide a class that contains a `Current` property, and `MoveNext` and `Reset` methods as described by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>, but the class does not have to implement <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>.
trans-unit.target: 使用 C# 开发时必须提供一个包含类`Current`属性，和`MoveNext`和`Reset`方法如下所述<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>，但类不必实现<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>。

trans-unit.source: The following code example demonstrates the best practice for iterating a custom collection by implementing the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> interfaces.
trans-unit.target: 下面的代码示例演示如何循环通过实现自定义集合的最佳做法<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>接口。

trans-unit.source: In this example, members of these interfaces are not explicitly called, but they are implemented to support the use of `foreach` (`For Each` in Visual Basic) to iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: 在此示例中，不显式调用这些接口的成员，但它们并实现以支持使用`foreach`(`For Each`在 Visual Basic 中) 以循环访问集合。

trans-unit.source: This example is a complete Console app.
trans-unit.target: 此示例是一个完整的控制台应用。

trans-unit.source: To compile the Visual Basic app, change the **Startup object** to **Sub Main** in the project’s **Properties** page.
trans-unit.target: 若要编译 Visual Basic 应用程序，更改**启动对象**到**Sub Main**在项目的**属性**页。

trans-unit.source: For a sample that shows how to implement the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> interface, see [Implementing the IEnumerable Interface in a Collection Class](https://code.msdn.microsoft.com/Implementing-the-e1708a24)
trans-unit.target: 有关示例，演示如何实现<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>接口，请参阅[在集合类中实现 IEnumerable 接口](https://code.msdn.microsoft.com/Implementing-the-e1708a24)

trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that iterates through a collection.
trans-unit.target: 返回循环访问集合的枚举数。

trans-unit.source: An <see cref="T:System.Collections.IEnumerator" /> object that can be used to iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: 一个可用于循环访问集合的 <see cref="T:System.Collections.IEnumerator" /> 对象。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`For Each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: C# 语言的 `foreach` 语句（在 Visual Basic 中为 `For Each`）隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> method also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>方法还会枚举器放回此位置。

trans-unit.source: At this position, the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> property is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>属性是不确定。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> method to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，必须调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>方法将枚举数前移到集合，然后再读取的值的第一个元素<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 在调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 或 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 之前，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 返回同一对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 若要再次将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素，可以调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 并接着调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举数没有对集合的独占访问权；因此，从头到尾对一个集合进行枚举在本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举过程中锁定集合。

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: 若要允许多个线程访问集合以进行读写操作，则必须实现自己的同步。

trans-unit.source: In this example, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable.GetEnumerator%2A> is not explicitly called, but it is implemented to support the use of `foreach` (`For Each` in Visual Basic).
trans-unit.target: 在此示例中，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable.GetEnumerator%2A>未显式调用，但其实现支持使用`foreach`(`For Each`在 Visual Basic 中)。
